7.1.5 - W11SR03: Ineffective Microsoft Cloud SaaS Backup and Versioning
ISM controls:
•	Control: 1515; Revision: 1; Updated: Sep-22; Applicability: All; OS: All (Backup of data in cloud services)
•	Control: 1516; Revision: 1; Updated: Sep-22; Applicability: All; OS: All (Restoration of data in cloud services)
•	Control: 1653; Revision: 0; Updated: Dec-23; Applicability: All; OS: All (Independent verification of data integrity in cloud services)
________________________________________
Current Risk
Insufficient or ineffective Microsoft cloud SaaS configurations, settings and version history backups, including point-in-time backups, to a secure, appropriately controlled, encrypted backup destination, may result in Windows 11 dependent systems being unavailable or unrecoverable in the event of a cloud tenancy compromise, malicious insider, or accidental configuration change.
Risk Assessment:
Risk Likelihood	x	Risk Consequence	=	Risk Rating
POSSIBLE	x	MAJOR	=	HIGH
________________________________________
Recommendations:
1.	Implement Independent SaaS Backup: Procure a third-party cloud-to-cloud backup solution to maintain immutable, encrypted copies of M365 data (Exchange, SharePoint, OneDrive) outside of the primary Microsoft ecosystem.
2.	Enforce Granular Point-in-Time Recovery: Configure automated daily backups with retention policies that satisfy agency Business Continuity Plan (BCP) requirements for point-in-time restoration.
3.	Establish Secure Backup Residency: Ensure the backup destination is geographically restricted to Australia and utilizes separate, hardened credentials to prevent a single tenant compromise from affecting backup integrity.
- Treatment #1
•	Third-Party Integration: Deploy a backup solution (e.g., Veeam or AvePoint) specifically designed for SaaS workloads to protect against accidental deletion or malicious encryption.
•	Verification Drills: Perform quarterly data restoration tests to verify the integrity of backed-up information and the effectiveness of the recovery process for Windows 11 dependent services.
•	Encryption Management: Ensure all backup data is encrypted at rest using agency-managed keys within a sovereign or appropriately controlled environment.
________________________________________
Residual risk outcome if recommendation is implemented.
Establishing an independent, off-site backup for SaaS data removes the reliance on Microsoft’s native recovery tools, which are often limited in scope. While the "Major" consequence of a system outage remains, the likelihood of permanent data loss or prolonged unavailability is reduced to "Rare."
Risk Likelihood	x	Risk Consequence	=	Risk Rating
RARE	x	MAJOR	=	MEDIUM

